President Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals for key administration posts. These include Michael J. McCord as Principal Deputy Under Secretary of Defense (Comptroller) at the Department of Defense, Katherine M. Gehl and Michael J. Warren as members of the Board of Directors of the Overseas Private Investment Corporation. President Obama also intends to appoint individuals to the Vietnam Education Fund and the President's Advisory Committee on the Arts for the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts. The nominees and appointees have diverse backgrounds and expertise in fields such as defense, investment, education, and the arts. President Obama commended their commitment to serving the country and looks forward to working with them.